ardinal.{v}</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`Subfield.relrank A B` is defined to be `[B : A ⊓ B]` as a `Cardinal`, in particular,\nwhen `A ≤ B` it is `[B : A]`, the degree of the field extension `B / A`.\nThis is similar to `Subgroup.relIndex` but it is `Cardinal` valued. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/FieldTheory/Relrank.html#Subfield.relrank","kind":"def","line":43,"name":"Subfield.relrank","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/FieldTheory/Relrank.lean#L43-L46"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.FieldTheory.IntermediateField.Adjoin.Basic"],"instances":[],"name":"Mathlib.FieldTheory.Relrank"}